---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Sustainability | About Heat & Glo"
  description="Heat & Glo's approach to sustainability: product longevity over disposability, serviceability over replacement cycles, efficient combustion over open-hearth waste. How Heat & Glo designs fireplaces to last and perform."
  noIndex={true}
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative mb-12 -mx-4">
    <img
      src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/c220ce20-e963-4c07-85ca-83fa16359ef4/Nest-Out-West-Basem?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:720"
      alt="Basement living space anchored by a Heat & Glo fireplace as the room's focal point"
      class="w-full object-cover"
      style="height: 400px;"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center px-8" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, rgba(0,0,0,0.88) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.62) 55%, rgba(0,0,0,0.18) 100%);">
      <div class="max-w-page mx-auto text-white">
        <p class="uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold drop-shadow" style="color: #fdba74;">Sustainability</p>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mt-3 max-w-2xl drop-shadow-lg leading-tight">Built to last. Built to recover.</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg max-w-xl drop-shadow" style="color: #e5e5e5;">Longevity over disposability. Serviceability over replacement cycles. This is how Heat & Glo approaches the long run.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-page mx-auto px-4 py-4">

    <!-- DIRECT ANSWER LEDE -->
    <header class="mb-16">
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-700 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        Heat & Glo's sustainability position is not a marketing layer. It is a product design philosophy. A fireplace that operates reliably for thirty years, with serviceable components that a dealer can replace in the field, contributes more to actual environmental outcomes than a cheaper alternative marketed as eco-friendly but designed to fail and be replaced. Durability and serviceability are the foundation. Everything else, from combustion efficiency to packaging material choices, builds from there.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- CORE PILLARS -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <p class="uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #c44a08;">The core position</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10" style="color: #1a1a1a;">Sustainability means the product outlasts the trend.</h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">

        <div style="border-left: 4px solid #c44a08; padding-left: 24px;">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: #1a1a1a;">Longevity over disposability</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">A fireplace is a permanent installation. It is not replaced on an appliance cycle. The environmental math on a durable product is straightforward: fewer manufacturing runs, fewer shipping cycles, less packaging consumed, less material going to landfill or recovery at end-of-life. Heat & Glo designs to a lifespan measured in decades, not years, which means the upfront resource investment in manufacturing each unit is spread across a longer service life. That is a fundamentally different sustainability calculation than a consumer electronics product, and it is one the hearth industry does not make enough noise about.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="border-left: 4px solid #c44a08; padding-left: 24px;">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: #1a1a1a;">Serviceability in the field</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">A product that can be repaired is more sustainable than a product that must be replaced. Heat & Glo fireplaces are designed with serviceable components: ignition systems, control boards, remote systems, and glass assemblies that a trained technician can diagnose and replace at your home without taking the unit out of the wall. The 1,400+ authorized dealers in the Heat & Glo network are also service partners. When your fireplace needs attention in year fifteen, the dealer who sold it has access to parts and the training to keep the original unit running. That is what the service network is for.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

        <div style="border-left: 4px solid #c44a08; padding-left: 24px;">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: #1a1a1a;">Domestic manufacturing</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Every Heat & Glo unit is manufactured in Lake City, Minnesota. Manufacturing in the US, close to the North American customer base, shortens the supply chain between production and installation. A shorter supply chain means less freight distance per unit, less packaging required for long-haul transport, and tighter quality oversight because the manufacturing facility and the engineering team are in the same building. This is not a gesture. It is how Heat & Glo has operated since 1975, and it carries real supply chain and environmental consequences that imported alternatives do not.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="border-left: 4px solid #c44a08; padding-left: 24px;">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: #1a1a1a;">Material recovery at end-of-life</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Fireplaces are primarily steel and cast iron, materials with established and efficient recovery paths at end-of-life. When a Heat & Glo unit eventually reaches the end of its service life after decades of use, the steel firebox and structural components can be recycled through conventional metal recovery. Heat & Glo's design emphasis on durability and repairability means that end-of-life moment arrives as late as possible. For questions about specific material composition or end-of-life guidance for a particular model, your authorized dealer or HHT's customer service team can provide product-specific information.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FULL-BLEED BAND: EFFICIENCY ARGUMENT -->
    <section class="relative -mx-4 mb-20">
      <img
        src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/d46ab388-275f-4983-b659-7c4cd454dcf5/img-pdp-mezzo-room-1?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:560"
        alt="Heat & Glo Mezzo contemporary linear gas fireplace with ribbon flame in a residential living room"
        class="w-full object-cover"
        style="height: 380px;"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center px-4" style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.52);">
        <div class="max-w-page mx-auto w-full">
          <div style="background: rgba(26,26,26,0.94); color: #fff; padding: 36px 40px; border-radius: 12px; max-width: 42rem; border: 1px solid #3a3a3a;">
            <p style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: #fdba74;">Combustion efficiency</p>
            <h2 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 10px; line-height: 1.35;">Direct-vent gas fireplaces and what sealed combustion actually means.</h2>
            <p style="margin-top: 14px; color: #d4d4d4; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 15px;">Heat & Glo's direct-vent gas fireplaces use a sealed combustion system: the firebox draws combustion air from outside the home through a dedicated air intake and exhausts combustion gases directly outside through a co-axial pipe. No inside air is consumed. No chimney draft is required. This sealed system delivers heat to the room rather than losing conditioned air up a flue. The result is a combustion appliance that warms the space it is in without the air exchange losses of an open fireplace, a traditional gas log set installed in an open hearth, or an older atmospheric-vent gas unit. For homeowners who heat primarily with a gas fireplace rather than as a supplemental source, the efficiency difference between a sealed direct-vent unit and an open-hearth alternative is material.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- EPA CERTIFICATION TIE-IN -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <p class="uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #c44a08;">For wood-burning fireplaces</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: #1a1a1a;">EPA certification and cleaner combustion.</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-8">For homeowners choosing a wood-burning fireplace, EPA certification represents the cleaner combustion end of the spectrum. Heat & Glo wood-burning fireplaces that carry EPA certification have been independently tested and verified to meet particulate matter emissions limits under the EPA's Step 2 standard, which went into full effect in 2020. A certified unit produces measurably less fine particulate matter (PM2.5) than a non-certified or uncertified alternative burning the same fuel load. This matters for indoor air quality, for neighborhood air quality, and for compliance in jurisdictions that require EPA-certified appliances for new installations.</p>

      <a href="/about-us/epa-certification/" style="display: inline-block; padding: 14px 28px; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 15px; border: 2px solid #c44a08; color: #c44a08;" onmouseover="this.style.background='#fff7ed'" onmouseout="this.style.background='transparent'">Read: How EPA Certification Works →</a>
    </section>

    <!-- OUTDOOR SECTION -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <p class="uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #c44a08;">Outdoor fire products</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: #1a1a1a;">Gas over open-fire alternatives, outdoors too.</h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">Outdoor fire products, from fire tables to log sets on covered patios, present the same combustion trade-off as indoor applications. Open wood fires outdoors produce the same particulate matter, in the same uncontrolled quantities, as open indoor hearths. Heat & Glo's outdoor gas fire products burn clean, with no wood particulate, no ash management, and no accumulation of combustion residue in an outdoor setting that lacks any venting system at all. The gas connection is a supply line and a control valve. The flame is consistent, adjustable, and ignites reliably without starter materials or weather dependency.</p>
          <a href="/fireplaces/?category=outdoor" style="display: inline-block; font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; color: #c44a08; text-decoration: none;">Browse outdoor fire products →</a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <img
            src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/4b548b1f-4515-4438-be37-975077ed748a/20_HHT_GasLogs_Outd?io=transform:fill,width:800,height:480"
            alt="Outdoor Heritage Oak gas logs by Heat & Glo installed on a covered patio"
            style="width: 100%; height: 300px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 12px;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA BAND: DEALER + PROADVANTAGE -->
    <section style="background: #fff7ed; border: 1px solid #fed7aa; border-radius: 12px; padding: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 24px; align-items: center;">
      <div>
        <p style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: #c44a08;">Long-term ownership</p>
        <h2 style="font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 8px; color: #1a1a1a;">Your dealer is your service partner for the life of the unit.</h2>
        <p style="color: #525252; margin-top: 10px; max-width: 34rem; line-height: 1.7;">Heat & Glo's 1,400+ authorized dealers handle installation, annual service, warranty work, and parts replacement for the long run. When something needs attention in year twelve, the same network is there.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="/where-to-buy/" style="background: #c44a08; color: #fff; display: inline-block; padding: 16px 32px; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 16px;" onmouseover="this.style.background='#a83e07'" onmouseout="this.style.background='#c44a08'">Find a Dealer →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECONDARY CTA: ProAdvantage -->
    <section style="border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 24px; align-items: center;">
      <div>
        <p style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: #c44a08;">For specifiers</p>
        <h2 style="font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 8px; color: #1a1a1a;">Sustainability documentation for your project.</h2>
        <p style="color: #525252; margin-top: 10px; max-width: 34rem; line-height: 1.7;">If you are specifying Heat & Glo for a project that requires sustainability documentation, emissions data, or material disclosure, the ProAdvantage trade program gives you direct access to spec sheets, installation manuals, and specification engineering support.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="/pro/" style="background: #1a1a1a; color: #fff; display: inline-block; padding: 16px 32px; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 16px;" onmouseover="this.style.background='#333'" onmouseout="this.style.background='#1a1a1a'">ProAdvantage Overview →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t pt-10">
      <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">
        <a href="/about-us/" class="underline font-medium">Back to About</a>
      </p>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
